	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				One thing I forgot to address that should be part of basic enchanter teachings:  Acting in a group.<BR>
<BR>
When you join a group, first thing you ask (unless you've been with them before) -- is if they have grouped with an enchanter before.  They need to understand how to program a /assist key, and assist whoever your &quot;designated hitter&quot; (normally your biggest tank) is...This way, the entire group is on ONE target.<BR>
<BR>
Your job, now, is to stand back, and mezz ANYTHING else that gets caught up in the frenzy.  The second incoming on a double pull, something caught in a AoE blast wave, anything that's whaping on your party except what they are hitting at the moment.<BR>
<BR>
Couple things to address.  It's not easy.  You'll find after you mez something, it's going to be wanting your blood when that mez breaks.  I ALWAYS (except in low mana/special situations) mem-blur after the mez.  Memory Blur wipes the monsters hate list (to an extent, i've never had it fail but .. i've heard if it's a really red mob, and you're really hated, it might take two applications) -- so after that mez breaks, it's not really going to care about you unless you're standing too close, and if it's a normally non-aggressive monster that was just caught in AoE of something, it'll wander off.<BR>
<BR>
Now, i've managed to mezz reds at most every level.  If it's yellow/red, except your mez to fail, and that bad thing to start whomping on you.  You can do a few things in this situation.  Color flux/re-mez can work.  If it mob hit you and now your pet is dealing with it, memblur it, and let your pet keep that busy, mez when/if the pet dies.  You can try mezzing while in Melee (hard to do, VERY likely of getting interrupted) .. You can memblur, make it step away, and then re-mezz...Root and mez and blur..You get the idea, be creative, and realize that your main function is to keep the extras off your group as long as you can.  Don't blow your mana on DD/DOT if you're currentally holding 2 or 3 targets in mezmorization -- you're asking to die.  If your tanks/casters are dealing good damage to that target, and not taking too much, let them move down the line, just keep that mez up (i often re-mez before the first one has broke, just to keep it stuck)..<BR>
<BR>
A few notes:<BR>
<BR>
Mez does not necessarally refer to mezmorize -- it referres to whatever mez line spell you are using.  My current is Enthrall, nice long hold!<BR>
<BR>
If you are with a group that has tanks/wizzen/others breaking your mezzes over and over again and getting you killed, leave!  If they can't understand how to /assist someone, you need to be with better players.  Sure, we can nuke pretty darn well, and in that nice single pull, I always throw some damage in just to take it down fast and keep my tanks from getting smacked on too much -- but our primary function, as I see it, in a group, is to reduce the overall damage potential -- we are the ONLY class that can take a accidental 4 or 5 even/yellow pull resulting in a total-party-death for the enchanterless group -- we can make that pull into a manageable (if a bit stressful) situation.  There was no better feeling for me in my EQ life when I managed to hold 3 mist elementals, 2 fire elementals, and a couple greater skellys in mez while my group took that Tentacle Terror down.  I got smacked on a lot, but no one died, and we managed to take a red, a even, and then 4 blues down, back to back, without anyone getting killed. That's what a enchanter does.  <BR>
<BR>
Teach your groupmates how we work, start realzing the power you have with mezmorise/memory-blur combos -- we're on of the few classes that can always have a really good shot at taking a certin death situationa and turning it around.  It's kinda embarassing to have a hard time soloing a blue at higher level, but once you get with a group and things go wrong and you start doing your thing, they will not want to take that camp without you there, trust me.<BR>
<BR>
And if all the pulls go well, you're still a damn good nuker, and you can keep those tanks buffed with quickness, the casters with breeze, and keep nuking those mobs.  I have a hard time playing my tank class characters now, hitting a and watching the blood fly is a little .... disenchanting to me.<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

